description: Angry Birds, everyone's most popular mobile game franchise, is now everyone's most popular mini-comic! This issue features our favorite flock of furious fowls in: "A Little Off The Top" and "Last One In" by Eisner award winner, Paul Tobin!
name: A Little Off the Top; Last One In

description:
A Family Affair

Father has revealed the truth of the program to Anya. Now aware of the stakes, and how little time they have, Anya determines that they must engage Ngeve and shut the program down once and for all. Guardian begins her training and although it won't be complete, it may give them a chance. As with all best laid plans, tragedy befalls the group, sending the mission into doubt.
name: A Family Affair

description:
When Archie wipes out while surfing a monster wave at Riverdale beach, he meets a beautiful rescuer with … fins and seashell accessories? She’s beautiful, rich, kind, and she takes Archie’s breath away—literally! Is Archie’s new discovery a friend or a siren? Will she bring Archie safely back to his friends, or will Riverdale be missing its favorite redhead? Find out in “Mermaid Service,” the lead story in this summery fun issue of Archie’s Funhouse Comics Digest!

Note: The digital edition (8/6/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Mermaid Service!

description:
All of Ariol's friends know that he has a big crush on Petula, but no one seems to notice that Bizbilla has her sights on Ariol, including Ariol! While she's waited in the . . . er, wings hoping Ariol will notice her, this sweet little fly has been cooking up a plan. Mister Cantharide, Bizbilla's dad, is an ophthalmologist. An ophthalmologist is the eye doctor. Ariol wears glasses. And it seems he has an appointment coming up! Bizbilla is all abuzz with impatience; will Ariol finally get the message?

With charming artwork and hilarious vignettes, ARIOL is the perfect series for anyone who started off life as a kid!

Story Titles

  • It's All Good
  • The Big Hug
  • After the Rain Comes Fair Weather
  • Riddles
  • In the CUCUFE Forest
  • ARIOL Defends Santa Claus
  • Another Report!
  • RIKA
  • The Tattooed Ear
  • RAMONO and SPELLERINO
  • Market Day at Saint-AMPOIRE
  • Thanks, BIZZBILLA!

Note: The digital edition (8/6/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Bizzbilla Hits the Bullseye

description: In order to more efficiently fight crime, Batman creates a Bat-Robot. But will the Caped Crusader's ingenuity make the real Batman unnecessary?
name: Chapter Fourty

description: The adventures continue! Boots has just about had it with Sniffles and delivers an ultimatum while Pup finds himself a new job - this time will he call the shots?
Help captive aboard the strange vessel, Loud Hawk and Two Songs plan their escape from the vicious Sargeant Hickock.

We the Pizza

Brandy Meadows of Slice Magazine learns the ways of the pizza boy from Chance and Super Cheese. Pia joins Turbo Pizza as the phone girl and we learn that OJ Simpson and Figgs have a history.
name: We the Pizza

description: It’s Quincredible versus Terrain round two! Yet the flow of the battle is turning more and more from Quincredible fighting to stop Terrain from hurting people to Quincredible stopping Terrain from harming himself. Unfortunately Terrain is more than determined to end it all right in front of Quinton and our hero may be powerless to stop him!

C*ck and P*ssy Eyed!

When life takes a cheap shot and you find yourself in County Holding neck deep in gang bangers, racists, junkies and pigs what do you do? If you're Colt Buckshot and Jackson Dupagne you play Yahtzee, dumbass.

Lines are drawn, blurred, crossed and redrawn and somewhere between a brilliant hypnotist and a hulking horny-eyed bastard, Colt and Jackson discover what fate is... and then they discover theirs!

Can these two peckerwoods be responsible for the fate of Humanity? Can they manage to roll their next joint? Can they find the hole in their ass without a GPS?

Ohh cruel FORTUNA!! What does your merciless wheel have in store for DOUBLE BARREL?!?
name: C*ck and P*ssy Eyed!

description:
Death of a Nation - Part 4

As The Civil Four march to the final conflict with The Dandy and his forces, a new an unexpected member joins the cause. Will this new warrior be enough to turn the tide? To the victor goes the nation to the loser only the shroud of death.
name: Death of A Nation Part 4

description:
Machine One

The machines lied to Dobbs. They told him he was the only human alive. But Dobbs has learned of at least one other ... And with that knowledge comes new purpose. Because if someone else is alive within Mech City, maybe there is reason for living. Maybe there is a way out of this hell.
name: Machine One

description:
ONE COMIC BOOK, THREE STORIES. WELCOME TO THE DOGHOUSE ISSUE FIVE.

"...AS IN KING ARTHUR. HOLY GRAIL. KNIGHTS OF THE ROUND TABLE. ALL THAT BOLLOCKS."

With two men missing, Willams finally comes face to face with the mysterious Merlin - in AVALON.

"OLD MAN LEVY. ABOUT 8FT TALL? PURPLE FACE?"

Welcome to Farland, Ohio - a small town whose world just got turned upside down - in FLIPSIDE.

"LITTLE WORK-OUT NEVER HURT ANYONE."

Jack has a lot on his shoulders when their latest repo job becomes an uphill struggle - in REPO DELUXE.
name: Avalon; Flipside; Repo Deluxe

description: Serialized from the pages of Dungeon Quest Book Three by Joe Daly, we join Millenium Boy, Millenium Boy, Steve, Nerd Girl and Lash Penis mid-adventure. In the best comic afterschool special, they light up a giant spliff of their "Orangutan Daydream" only to suffer some serious side effects.

In a final desperate move to cling to power amid the scandal of the Opposition Assassinations, President Reyes declares Martial Law.

The Filipino Heroes League believe that by doing so the President has fallen into a carefully laid trap constructed by the Touch and his cronies.

Before the President falls even deeper into the Touch's schemes, the FHL draw up a desperate plan to save him.

They plan to kidnap him.
name: The Sword

description:
Tales Of Again/Forward

They're still making these?! YES! Back after much critical acclaim, apparently it's Freestyle time! The comic no-one thought would make it past the first issue yet here it is at number 09! Created by Australian Mark Pursell who likes to think he can draw and write and stuff and occasionally can, Freestyle is a comic. It is funny and has words and pretty pictures!

The back and forth continues as Stupid and the gang fight over who exactly is the bad guy. Did I say who? It could also mean what as more revelations are revealed, endings began and further adventure hinted at.

Let's do this! You won't be disappointed too much!
name: Tales Of Again/Forward

description:
Reflections on Climate Change

There is change in the air, but the kind only noticed by those who create it... and those who must stop it. Captain Sanders finds an outlet for some of his anger just before Rondo reveals the truth that belies his undercurrent of rage.

Within a secret chamber underground, known as the Bridge, Professor Marwyn reveals to Cunctato who really controls the weather.

Meanwhile, at the ranch of Theo Soell, the sheriff ponders the ironic mystery of life, proving that one good cattle mutilation deserves another.

And, the news continues to subdue the masses with tales of lust and murder.
name: Reflections On Climate Change

description: Esther's reputation takes a knock, Susan Ptolemy can't get a good night's sleep, and Daisy just wants to fit in. She is never going to fit in.

Kids Bless The Darndest Things

In which Carol tastes vengeance and finds her calling in public speaking.
name: Kids Bless The Darndest Things

description:
Creators: Half stories for dog-lovers, half for cat-lovers. Original stories and poems by Ray Bradbury, P.G. Wodehouse, Algernon Blackwood, Robert E. Howard, Franz Kafka, Saki, Edward Lear, Joe R. Lansdale, Carl Sandburg, Joseph Jacobs, H.P. Lovecraft, Ambrose Bierce, Robert J, Burdette, James Anthony Froude, O. Henry, Oliver Goldsmith, John Lehman. Adaptations by Alex Burrows, Antonella Caputo, Trina Robbins, Tom Pomplun. Edited by Tom Pomplun and John Lehman. Comics and illustrations by Randy DuBurke, Evert Geradts, Shepherd Hendrix, John Findley, Jeff Bonivert, Jim McMunn, Shary Flenniken, Hunt Emerson, Senthil Kumar, Milton Knight, Neale Blanden, Dragan Kovacevic, Lisa K. Weber, Vincent Stall, Mary Fleener, Lance Tooks, Skot Olsen, Pat Lewis, Allen Koszowski, Peter Kuper. Covers by Toni Pawlowsky. Canine/Feline Classics is a unique, two-in-one volume, with half stories for dog-lovers, and half for cat-lovers. Featured are "The Emissary" by Ray Bradbury, "Ancient Sorceries" by Algernon Blackwood, "The Beast from the Abyss" by Robert E. Howard, and 17 more great stories and poems, including two from the volume's co-editor, John Lehman.

Note: The digital edition (8/6/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Canine/Feline Classics

description: In brief, Gutters is a series of standalone pages that parody the comic book industry and the heroes and characters that dwell within. Think of it as an editorial cartoon targeting comic books, and you'll understand where we're going with it. Gutters is written by Ryan Sohmer, with Lar deSouza as Art Director and Ed Ryzowski serving as colorist. As for who will be doing the actual art, well, that's where things get interesting (and slightly different). Rather than have one artist pencil each page, we elected to have a rotating roster of professional artists, among them some giants in the comic book industry alongside new and emerging talent.

Dalton Treethorn makes a shocking discover, Dr Pontarius is no more, and the new heroes feel themselves being drawn together by something unseen!

Includes a back up story by Rich Lovatt and Michael Lee Harris.

Road Warriors

In post-apocalyptic Canada, guns don't kill people - slapshots do.

For the mutated tribes trying to survive nuclear winter - which is like normal Canadian winter, just more radioactive - hockey serves as a form of ritual warfare in which communities gamble their resources on the abilities of their squad to score goals and bust heads on the ice.

Join the Edmonton Atomics - Skully, Squid, Stretch, and Ugly Dave - as they face off with the Calgary Cataclysms one more time, with the fate of a community on the line.
name: Road Warriors

description: One evening in France, a meteorite crashed and a new and strange plant was discovered. The next day, everyone forgot this event, except certain people, such as Adrien. Adrien decides to fight the plant because it hurts his girlfriend. Will Adrien reach his goal to kill the plant, or will his oponents stop him?

Part one of a two-parter featuring King Leo as he tracks down the soul of a man lost in the Barrens. King Leo loses himself along the way and finds it harder to get back to his mortal body. What he discovers on the other side, however, is much worse than what he'd been witness to in our world. Duran and Beckett have disappeared and it will take all of King Leo's power to track them down and save this lost soul.
name: The Barrens Part 1 of 2

description: Have you ever held a cell phone in your hand that you believed could fulfill your dreams? What if there was one that could give you ultimate power? The Kami Kaze couple is after this phone to protect it from falling into the wrong hands. But nothing in this world is as simple as it seems...
name: Peter Pan Syndrome

description:
Baron Kah Lee's ever expanding war has finally reached the doorstep of Pale's home, Chuh Nar. Our young hero has left the safety of his city sanctuary in order to confront the vile Baron.

Attempting to save his parents and home from enslavement, Pale has unwittingly played right in the Baron's plans.
name: Rise of the Ape King Chapter Three

description: The Kingstone Bible is the most complete graphic adaptation of the Bible ever done. Volume 4 covers Samson and the book of Judges.
name: The Judges

description: The Kingstone Bible is the most complete graphic adaptation of the Bible ever done. Volume 7 covers the fall of Jerusalem, daniel, Ezra, Nehemiah and Esther.
name: The Exile

description: The hunt continues for Brand while Lawton finds vengeance.

At one time, the magnificent Empire of Rome stood as the pillar of the Western Civilization. But as the city began to crumble, those responsible needed a way out. From the shadow would come salvation, but there is always a price for freedom.
name: In the Shadows of Rome

description: Les “Survivorman” Stroud’s abilities are continually tested as his pursuit of the Horn of Providence leads him to the English Moors. Les, his son Logan, and sidekick Cro Magnon face wolves, severe weather, and a rotating cast of villain Oswald Good’s “assistants.” All of this awaits you in issue #3!

Desperation

Desperate for an ally, M3 goes to the most unlikely of people: Morris. Will he be able to put their pasts aside and help? And we gain insight into the event that led Machiavella to the path of assassin. Cover art by father and son team Chris Notarile TD and Chris R. Notarile.
name: Desperation

description:
Everybody Steals Something Sometime.

Events escalate when Andrea turns to Mack for some career advice.
name: Everybody Steals Something Sometime.

description:
On the Ricochet

Having solved the mystery--although perhaps not the mystery he was hired to solve--McBlack gathers everyone together for the most violent parlour-room denouement in the history of crime fiction.
name: On the Ricochet

description: Crockett drives to meet with Pasqual's men while Tubbs and Zito monitor from a distance. At the hospital an assassin attempts to kill the team's star witness but Castillo and the team fight them off. Sonny receives a message that the meet location has been moved… to Cape Canaveral.
Lucifer, Remiel, Michael and Ariel must escape from the heart of the Daemon's den. Even if they survive, what awaits them in Heaven may be even more shocking.

Campfires I

Tholemo convinces Corben to make camp for the night. Corben recounts the story of how he came to find The Tome of Thanatos by following clues left by his late father, Erasthmus.
name: Campfires I

description:
Disappearing Acts

Penny Palabras, 17, is being tormented by the Straw Man. The Ghost Librarian is trying to help her get to the bottom of things, while Penny's made deals with both the Pawn Broker and a Tiger Devil. The Pawn Broker loaned her the Spectacular Revolver and is interested in collecting valuable artifacts, but the Tiger Devil's motives aren't as clear. Penny's been expelled from school for skipping class with only weeks left before graduation, and her mother is undertandably angry. Penny's in a dark place, but the Ghost Librarian offers her a bit of respite, even if it does come with a cost. Her nightmares won't let her sleep, her friends and family can't understand, and the Straw Man is getting more powerful every day.
name: Disappearing Acts

description:
Traveling back through time to the age of the dinosaurs, young adventurers Patrice Blazing and Nate Timely face unexpected threats in the past! Racing to beat Zomboss before the zombie leader can recover all the parts he needs to rebuild the deadly Sun Vacuum, our heroes must work together—and with Crazy Dave—to fend off a “fun-dead” invasion that threatens all ages! Paul Tobin (Bandette, Prometheus) and Ron Chan (The Guild, Husbands) deliver the third chapter in their hilarious Plants vs. Zombies: Timepocalypse series!

The hit video game returns to comics!

A humor-filled adventure that all ages can enjoy!

A new Plants vs. Zombies comic-book series!

“Brains? If you have them, we’d like to invite you on this . . . most delicious adventure.”—Dr. Zomboss

In this issue, Dave, Patrice, and Nate travel back to the time of the dinosaurs--but Dave ends up going back to the future and forgetting about his niece and her friend. Nate is in initially excited about seeing dinosaurs, but eventually gets scared. They find a zombie camp, and realize that they have been looking for the sun vacuum part for hundreds of years. How could Patrice and Nate find it? Only by Nate accidentally sitting on it, of course. Now all they need is for Dave to remember to pick them up.

Henry and Punky are finally having an adoption hearing, but a know-it-all civil servant is trying to ship Punky back to foster care. Punky enlists her friends to vouch for the power of their nontraditional family, but it’s not going well. It’s time for Punky to take her stand by taking the stand!
name: Bad Hearing

description:
PSE-Trent

Quad is a series of four stories set in the same post-apocalypse universe.

This is the number two of four.

-

In one of the last known cities of the world, robots are the man's best friend.

When a robot breaks one the three rules, it means it is possessed by an ancient virus.

Well, that's why we have the Paranormal Software Exorcists, after all.
name: PSE-Trent

description:
Manga Contents

  • Mr. Bird

School Boy Error

Our unfortunate hero, Gazzer, avoided being beaten up by a gang of neds only to be abducted and taken to Mars.

With the help of a priest and glamour model, Gazzer managed to escape.

While searching for a way back to Earth the group come face to face with Lord Veset, an evil intergalactic entrepreneur who claims to have discovered "eternal life".
name: School Boy Error

description:
Forgotten Lore

Nightwatcher Corvan Moore gets pulled into the Veil of the Otherworld by the celestial who calls himself, The Albatross. With Zalaphir's help, Corvan finally uncovers many secrets of his past--they aren't enough. Corvan will have to dive deeper in order to prevent the greatest threat Cog Town will ever face.
name: Forgotten Lore

description:
No-Tell Motel

The Grand Finale.
name: No-Tell Motel

description: As the Sentinels regroup from the events of the confrontation with Damien, the government organization known as the Order prepares to make their move.

Throughout the decades, The Shadow has served as a timeless agent of justice, bringing death and disaster to tyrants and criminals alike. During the decadent 1980s, this mysterious Master of Men faced perhaps his deadliest opponents yet: the Seven Deadly Finns, a crime family gripping New York City in a stranglehold. When The Shadow's network of agents applies pressure to their vast operations, the Finn brothers push back, enlisting serial killers and terrorists into their ranks. The violence escalates, leading to an explosive confrontation atop the Empire State Building and a shock ending which no one - not even The Shadow - could know!
name: The Seven Deadly Finns, Part 4: Prime Time

description:
Team-Up Part Four

As Ofer (Enormous) visits his father Branch meets with Blaze while Splendour and Swift discover something new about each other!

It's adventure and questing galore in this installment in the acclaimed Sonic Archives series! Sonic fights for his life against, not one, but two robot doubles! Is the armor to Silver Sonic II really unbreakable? Is the latest Metal Sonic truly faster than the Blue Blur? Its up to Sonic and Tails to find out for sure! Meanwhile, Rotor makes a dangerous trek home to find the fate of his people. Monkey Khan is forced to relive his tragic past while a village of innocent lives hangs in the balance! And Knuckles begins to recover from the assault on Angel Island with some surprising and familiar faces! Sonic Archives 23 collects Sonic the Hedgehog #85-88.

Note: The digital edition (8/6/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Volume 23

description:
Chapter 5 pt 1

Ally is called by her cousin to talk care of some things back home.
name: Responsibilities Part 1

description:
Harlan Ellison’s Hugo- and WGA Award-winning teleplay, visualized for the first time! Stranded in the past of old Earth, Captain Kirk and Mr. Spock search for the focal point that altered the timestream and changed everything about the universe they knew. And once they find her, they could find themselves foiled by a force even greater than the Guardians of Forever—love!

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location
RegRegular CoverJuan Ortiz1
SubSubscription CoverPaul Shipper2

Note: The digital edition (8/6/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

volume.name: Star Trek: Harlan Ellison's Original The City On the Edge of Forever Teleplay

description: Devan wants to help Anneli escape. Anneli wants to kill Devan. The bounty hunters want to kill them both! Plus, Don Maximus sees an opportunity following a setback.
name: Revelation

description:
SLAUGHTERHOUSE! The crew of the Lost Light are used to past decisions coming back to bite them, but nothing—not even an ULTRA MAGNUS-certified crash course in the law of unintended consequences—could have prepared them for the horrors of Sector 113. Be warned: this issue is not for the easily distressed—or the easily heartbroken. A DAWN OF THE AUTOBOTS title!

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location
RegRegular CoverAlex Milne (a) & Josh Perez (c)1
SubSubscription CoverNick Roche (a) & Josh Burcham (c)2
RI30th Anniversary Retailer Incentive CoverCasey Coller (a) & John-Paul Bove (c)3

Note: The digital edition (8/6/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Slaughterhouse

volume.name: The Transformers: More Than Meets the Eye

description:
Satisfaction

Previously in Velica, Syxx Jones was caught off guard and tried to capture Velica without incident. But he failed miserably and found himself chasing her through the alleys and under the Ashton City Viaduct. Later, Domino is dining with his newest lieutenant Andrew Lounton, the UK club boss. Now, his past has come back to haunt him.
name: Satisfaction

description: On inspection of the so-called Video Nasties, Detective Gorely is finding it hard to believe that there is a link to be found to the string of murders... until a third body is discovered.

Follow Beryl as he explores the recesses of his subconscious and has to decide what is real and what is imagined. Is there a difference? Beryl will have to find out or risk falling into a metaphysical abyss from which he may not be able to come back from.
Zaya is called back to duty, much to her regret, and the mysterious killer takes another high-profile target.

name: The Fur King and Out of the Past: 9/27/39 10 12/19/39

description:
Pigs

When humans escape the Sunny Brookes slaughterhouse, a troubled pig finds the courage to help one stay free.
name: Pigs

volume.name: Illustrated Stories of the Operas: Rigoletto

description:
The Escapist

Begin Mayflower's first arc as you join the scientist named Roger Fergal as he plummets towards Earth in the midst of a terrorist attack. You'll soon find yourself in the ESG Preserves - a serene nature habitat suspended between skyscrapers and the place where the people who will change the Sol System forever first come together.
name: The Escapist

description:
Mr. Kawase’s life turns completely upside down when fellow teacher, Mr. Kazama, confesses he’s in love with Kawase! Kawase is a high school art teacher who has never once fallen in love. So when handsome goofball Kazama asks him out, Kawase agrees, thinking Kazama is just up to his usual pranks, but he soon realizes Kazama’s declaration of love is no joke. Through a series of exciting and sometimes heart-breaking encounters with his colleagues and students, Kawase learns what it means to love and be loved, and how to live with a love and life not readily accepted by society.

Contents

  • An Unforgettable Birthday
  • The First Summer
  • The First Winter
  • Mellow
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: After School In The Teacher's Lounge: The First Summer

description:
Billy is the guitarist for a relatively unknown band called The Idiots. On a fateful Wednesday, two perceived unrelated events occurred: (1) his idol passed away, and (2) his roommate stole both his money and guitar. Surrounding these two events is a series of chance meetings, painful realizations, excessive alcoholism, listlessness, flashbacks, and love. This is a terribly poignant story defining the unyielding love found between a vocalist and his guitarist.

Included with this manga are a couple of side stories. One is a story of the fantastical love between an artist and his subject. The other is a story of childhood friends turned lovers and their journey through life.
name: Vol. 1

description: When weather control experiments go horribly awry, a daring young scientist must face his personal demons to stop a deadly man-made storm of his own creation. Brainstorm takes you deep into the vortex and beyond -- featuring art by Dennis Calero (X-Men Noir).
A mysterious woman is strangely protective over the children of the local park.

person_credits.name: Angela Flatt
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, letterer, cover, other

description: Becca sneaks into a lavish wedding to get revenge on the groom, Alex, by exposing the truth—that he's heartlessly tossed aside her pregnant sister. However, someone stops her right as she decides to take action. When she turns to see who it is, she is confronted by a very handsome man. She is unaware that he is Christos, the head of Alex Carides’ family. The paparazzi witness the commotion, and as Becca and Christos escape, she wonders if she has mistaken him for a security guard….
name: Vol. 1

description: After defeating an evil wizard, Jim Parker and Karl Latimer suddenly find themselves being pursued by a secret government organization over an artifact they may not even have. With the wizard's apprentice in tow, the two must dodge the agents as well as a vampire street gang. Luckily, Karl has the power to transform into a demon while Jim has the uncanny ability to make any situation worse. Will they survive and, more importantly, will they get paid?

volume.name: The Dark Tower: The Drawing of the Three Sampler

description: Batman's 75th anniversary is here, and to celebrate, DC Entertainment is offering a series of promotionally priced specials that capture the Dark Knight's greatest moments! Frank Miller's all-time classic adventure kicks things off, with this excerpt from the original DARK KNIGHT RETURNS #1!

volume.name: DC Comics Essentials: Batman: The Dark Knight Returns

description: Follow-up to the Deadworld: Requiem for the World graphic novel. Mankind find itself trapped in a world of the walking dead and the living who will do anything to survive. The promise of "Safe Haven" reveals a much darker and sinister purpose, when victims find themselves in a medical facility, a "Slaughterhouse," which will stop at nothing to combat the zombie plague, including using humans as guinea pigs. Survivors find that the greatest horror may not be the zombies - but their own kind! Collects issues 1-4.
name: TPB

description: You enjoy Debaser? But do you know the hidden stories behind the adventures of Josh, Anna, Nathan and Rel? Find all Debaser's dirty secrets in these digital short stories!

In the climactic finale of Devil's Triangle, Gist Miller and what few are left of the original crew scramble aboard a purgatorial prison posing as a cruise ship set adrift. When Master Mahan, the ancient demon hell-bent on upgrading bodies, brings their pursuit to a head, Gist and friends must abandon their futile flight, and stand to face him. But lurking amidst angry phantom and zombie sailors, an even greater threat awaits them on the pitching deep-a threat spanning to biblical times. Caught up in a twister of good versus evil, Gist must find out what it really means to face the devil or lose everything he loves.
name: TPB

volume.name: Devil's Triangle: The Complete Graphic Novel

description: Dexter returns in an all-new, all-Australian, blood-soaked adventure written by his creator, Jeff Lindsay! Dexter Morgan isn't just Miami's No. 1 forensic blood-splatter expert - he's also a serial killer who targets other serial killers! But when Dexter travels Down Under on the trail of a new murderer, he quickly discovers that sharks aren't Australia's only deadly predator! Who is setting up illegal hunting safaris in the Outback, and are they targeting more than big game? Dexter investigates as only he can, but soon discovers that he isn't the hunter - he's the prey! Now Dexter is trapped in a private preserve where humans are in the crosshairs! Will this one end with a bang? Under the hot Australian sun, Dexter's Dark Passenger is given free reign, blood will flow, and the guilty will not go unpunished! Collecting DEXTER DOWN UNDER #1-5.
name: HC

description: San Francisco, the twentieth century: In 1939, a private detective searches for a missing heiress. In 1969, twin brothers approach a drug heist from opposite sides of the law. And in 1999, a woman slowly comes to realize the terrible danger she faces in her own home. From the Eisner-nominated writer DEREK McCULLOCH (STAGGER LEE, Gone To Amerikay) and artist ANTHONY PERUZZO comes DISPLACED PERSONS, a riveting tale of murder, love, crime, friendship, betrayal, and just the slightest bit of time travel.
name: OGN

description: In the housing projects of Southeast DC during the late 70's, a large portion of children started to develop Super-human abilities. Fed up with the lives they were born into, and wanting something more, they decided to take their piece of the American Dream, anyway they could.

Millie is a fledgling artist from London. She goes to Australia to put her artwork in a gallery while she works another job, but doesn't end up selling any of her work. One night, she is outside the gallery when young, handsome millionaire Levander approaches her. When he finds out she’s returning home the following day, he asks, “Would you like to make this last night a special night?” and then shows her around Melbourne. At first she feels uncomfortable—sightseeing with a man she just met! But she’s on a nice date with a handsome man, and she can’t stop her pounding heart!
name: Vol. 1

description:
Manga Contents

  • Mr. Bird

Five classic Jack London tales presented in a comic book format. Here are the stories of 'A Piece of Steak', 'Chinago', 'The Death of Ligoun', 'Tales of the Drooling Ward', and 'Koolau the Leper'. From comic book artist veterans Guy Davis, Vince Locke, Ron McCain, and Charles Yates.
name: TPB

description: The opening chapter of Sasha Janowicz' The Kursk. The story begins as the crew embark on their fateful journey.
name: Chapter 1

description: Amber has a crush on her boss, Bradley, the wealthy son of a family who owns an oil company. He seems so far above her and they haven't even spoken once, but for Amber it was love at first sight. One day there's an emergency and Bradley asks Amber to drive him to the hospital. His grandmother, the chairman of the board, is in critical condition. Amber waits for him in the hospital corridor, and when he emerges from the ICU his face is pale, and he asks her, "For my grandmother's sake, will you be my fiancée?"
name: Vol. 1

description: Lilly flies to Istanbul to appeal to Rauf Kasabian in person, an investor in her family’s travel company. He is suing the company for allegedly failing to pay its dividends, but she is unaware of any fraud. Rauf, who has gorgeous hazel eyes, coldly abandons her right after taking her virginity because he sees her as a wicked, calculating woman. Unbeknownst to Lilly, he plans to manipulate her for his own desires, thinking she is a fraud and a crook…!
name: Vol. 1
